# ── OpenTickly (Time Tracker) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses shared PostgreSQL (DB: opentickly) and shared Redis (db 3).

# Port for local testing — set in root .env
# OPENTICKLY_PORT=8082

# ── OpenTickly MCP (native FastMCP, #17) ──────────────────────────────────
# MCP server for Hermes. All keys live in the ROOT .env (already in the root
# .env.example) — set them there, not here. Full guide:
# services/opentickly/mcp/README.md.
#
# OPENTICKLY_MCP_TOKEN        (required) OpenTickly (Toggl) API token; mapped in
#   docker-compose.yml to the server's TOGGL_API_TOKEN. Generate in the
#   OpenTickly UI: Profile -> API token.
# OPENTICKLY_MCP_PORT         (optional) local-test host port for the MCP
#   container (empty on Dokploy; subdomain mcp-opentickly.dashboard.example.com
#   -> 8000 set in the Dokploy UI).
# OPENTICKLY_MCP_WORKSPACE_ID (optional) pin the workspace id; empty = the
#   account's default workspace (resolved via GET /api/v9/me on first call).
#
# Server-side vars (set by compose, not by you):
#   OPENTICKLY_BASE_URL=http://opentickly:8080  (internal upstream)
#   TOGGL_API_TOKEN=<- OPENTICKLY_MCP_TOKEN
#   OPENTICKLY_WORKSPACE_ID=<- OPENTICKLY_MCP_WORKSPACE_ID
